# --- Evidence corpus policy (FS.GG.Governance) -------------------------------
# This repo commits governance evidence AS THE AUDIT RECORD OF RECORD by design
# — that is the repo's purpose. The durable-vs-transient boundary (per the SDD
# transient-artifact taxonomy, FS-GG/FS.GG.SDD#110 / this repo #85) is:
#
#   DURABLE — intentionally committed, do NOT gitignore:
#     * surface-drift baselines (surface/**, *.txt) — these ARE the api-compat
#       contract and the surface-drift gate's source of truth;
#     * golden fixtures + snapshots (tests/**/goldens, **/snapshots) — pinned
#       expected output the tests compare against;
#     * .fsgg/*.yml sample + fixture config (governance/policy/capabilities/
#       tooling/release) — authored inputs, not run output;
#     * SDD artifacts (specs/*/spec.md, plan.md, tasks.md, contracts, research).
#
#   TRANSIENT — machine-regenerated per run, never committed (ignored below):
#     * specs/<feature>/readiness/ — per-run readiness evidence (0 committed
#       here; no per-feature re-inclusion whack-a-mole, unlike Rendering);
#     * .fsgg/*.json — CLI-emitted run outputs (gates.json, evidence.json,
#       evidence-reuse.json); the .fsgg *inputs* are .yml and stay committed.
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------

# Per-feature readiness evidence is transient test output (written into
# specs/<feature>/readiness/); regenerated on every run, never committed.
specs/*/readiness/

# CLI-emitted evidence run outputs (never committed; .fsgg/*.yml inputs are).
# **/ so it matches whether the tool runs at the repo root or inside a
# sample/fixture .fsgg/ dir.
**/.fsgg/*.json

# macOS / Linux cruft
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.tmp
*.swp

# Agent memory / session data (not a project deliverable)
.claude/projects/
